First note the common denominator is x + 3.  Combine the numerators:

\[
\frac{x^2}{x+3}-\frac{9}{x+3}
=\frac{x^2-9}{x+3}
\]

Factor the numerator:

\[
\frac{(x-3)(x+3)}{x+3}
= x-3,\quad x\neq -3.
\]

First observe that  
  5–2x = –(2x–5).  
Hence  
  \frac{2x}{5–2x} = –\frac{2x}{2x–5}.  
So  
  \frac{8x–15}{2x–5} + \frac{2x}{5–2x}  
= \frac{8x–15}{2x–5} – \frac{2x}{2x–5}  
= \frac{(8x–15) – 2x}{2x–5}  
= \frac{6x–15}{2x–5}  
= \frac{6(x–\tfrac52)}{2(x–\tfrac52)}  
= 3,  
provided 2x–5≠0 (i.e. x≠5/2).
